The paper is about a deep learning approach for salient object detection, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a compact and efficient network, which involves techniques such as residual learning and top-down attention, indicating that it may be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on benchmark datasets, suggesting that it may also be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
